# 🎫 IT Ticket Triage — OpenEnv Environment

[![OpenEnv](https://img.shields.io/badge/OpenEnv-Compliant-blue.svg)](https://github.com/openenv/spec)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Backends](https://img.shields.io/badge/LLM-Groq%20%7C%20Gemini%20%7C%20OpenAI-orange.svg)]()

An enterprise-grade, OpenEnv-compliant AI environment for IT support ticket triage.
Built for agent training and evaluation using a **regret-based RL reward signal** and a **hybrid agentic architecture**.

### 🚀 Live Demo & Repository
- **Hugging Face Space**: [Iamnetra/Triage_shadow](https://huggingface.co/spaces/Iamnetra/Triage_shadow)
- **GitHub Repository**: [NetraGurav/triage_shadow_system_meta](https://github.com/NetraGurav/triage_shadow_system_meta)

---

## ⚡ Key Features

- 🏎️ **Ultra-fast Triage**: Support for Groq (Llama 3.3) and Gemini 1.5 for sub-second triage.
- 🛡️ **Robust Fallback**: Automatically cascades from LLM providers to a local SFT baseline.
- 📊 **Shadow RL**: Dense reward signals derived from exhaustive action-space evaluation.
- 🧩 **Multi-head Classification**: Simultaneous prediction of Category, Priority, and Routing.
- 🧪 **Task-level Evaluation**: 24 curated scenarios across Easy, Medium, and Hard task levels.

## Environment Description

### What it simulates

Real-world IT helpdesk ticket triage — the process of reading an incoming support
ticket and making three critical decisions:

1. **Category** — What type of issue is this? (hardware, software, network, access, security)
2. **Priority** — How urgent is it? (P1 critical → P4 minor)
3. **Route** — Which team should handle it? (hardware\_team, dev\_team, network\_team, auth\_team, security\_team)

This is a genuine task performed thousands of times daily at every enterprise IT
department. Accurate triage reduces resolution time and prevents critical issues
from being buried.

### Why it matters

Mis-triaged tickets cause cascading failures: a ransomware alert routed to the
hardware team wastes hours. A P4-rated production outage misses SLA deadlines.
This environment lets agents learn the nuances of ticket classification under
ambiguity, multi-issue scenarios, and time pressure signals.

