## Setup Instructions

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. Run evaluation (SFT model — no API key needed)

```bash
python inference.py
```

### 3. Run evaluation (LLM agent)

The agent supports multiple backends. Default preference order: **Groq > Gemini > OpenAI**.

**Option A: Groq (Recommended for Speed)**
```bash
export MODEL_NAME="llama-3.3-70b-versatile"
export GROQ_API_KEY="gsk_..."
python inference.py --agent llm
```

**Option B: Gemini**
```bash
export MODEL_NAME="gemini-1.5-flash"
export GEMINI_API_KEY="AIza..."
python inference.py --agent llm
```

**Option C: OpenAI / Custom / OpenRouter**
```bash
export API_BASE_URL="https://api.openai.com/v1"
export MODEL_NAME="gpt-4o-mini"
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."  # or HF_TOKEN
python inference.py --agent llm
```

### 4. Start the API server

```bash
python app.py
# Server starts at http://localhost:7860
# Gradio UI at http://localhost:7860/ui
# API endpoints: POST /reset, POST /step, GET /state, GET /health
```

# Verify specific backend connectivity
python test_groq_call.py
python test_gemini_call.py
python test_openrouter.py

# Evaluate a single task
python inference.py --task easy

# Evaluate a specific ticket
python inference.py --ticket H001

# Train and save the SFT model (with LOO cross-validation)
python train.py --eval

# Quiet mode (summary only)
python inference.py --quiet
```

---

## Docker

```bash
# Build
docker build -t it-triage-openenv .

# Run (starts API server)
docker run -p 7860:7860 it-triage-openenv

# Run inference only (SFT agent)
docker run it-triage-openenv python inference.py

# Run inference (LLM agent)
docker run \
  -e API_BASE_URL="https://api.openai.com/v1" \
  -e MODEL_NAME="gpt-4o-mini" \
  -e HF_TOKEN="sk-..." \
  it-triage-openenv python inference.py --agent llm
```

